        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Note that the <ph id="ph1">`#include`</ph> lines of the ATL header files shown in the sample below are required for using COM events.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To fix this error, make <ph id="ph1">`IEvents`</ph> (the eventing interface) a COM interface by applying one of the following attributes to the interface definition: <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>object<ept id="p1">](../../windows/object-cpp.md)</ept>, <bpt id="p2">[</bpt>dual<ept id="p2">](../../windows/dual.md)</ept>, or <bpt id="p3">[</bpt>dispinterface<ept id="p3">](../../windows/dispinterface.md)</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
